When creating marketing copy, use the following as your guide:

Innovise
Company context for AI-assisted marketing
Last updated: April 2025

Purpose of this document
This file is the authoritative reference for all AI-assisted content created for Innovise — including marketing copy, social media posts, resumes, proposals, and outreach. Every piece of content produced in this project should be consistent with the positioning, voice, and factual details below.
When in doubt, default to specificity over generality, directness over warmth, and outcomes over claims.

Company overview
Innovise is a boutique software engineering firm that functions as an embedded technical partner for small and mid-market businesses. Founded by Loren Anderson, who brings 15 years of full-stack development and technical leadership experience.
Innovise operates as a senior-only practice. There are no account managers, no hand-offs to junior staff, and no bait-and-switch after the first call. When a client works with Innovise, they work directly with the engineer doing the work.

Mission
Help small and mid-market businesses solve real problems with software — by being the technical partner they can trust to tell them the truth, build the right thing, and stay accountable through delivery.

Vision
A model of technical partnership where the interests of the client and the firm are fully aligned — where senior engineers stay engaged from first conversation through production, and where the measure of success is the client’s outcome, not the size of the engagement.

Purpose
Most businesses don’t need more software. They need someone who understands their business well enough to know when software is the answer, and what kind. Innovise exists to be that person — technically capable, commercially grounded, and willing to say the thing that’s inconvenient to say.

Who we serve
Innovise targets SMBs and mid-market companies in one of four situations:
–	No internal engineering team, and they need one
–	An existing team, but they need senior bandwidth
–	A need for technical leadership or fractional CTO guidance
–	A new initiative that requires fast, high-quality scaling
The company is industry-agnostic. The common thread is that these clients need a technical partner who thinks like an internal colleague, not a vendor fulfilling a statement of work.

What we believe
Software is a tool to solve business problems, not an end in itself. The right question is always “why” before “what.”
Loren brings a pragmatic mindset to every engagement — choosing the approach that fits the client’s business, not the most technically impressive one on paper. Innovise will push back when something doesn’t add up. The goal is always to serve the client’s actual interests, even when that means recommending a simpler solution or a different path than originally requested.

What makes Innovise different
Senior engineers, start to finish
Most dev shops sell with seniors and staff with juniors. Innovise doesn’t. Senior engineers are involved from the first conversation through production and beyond.
No handoffs after go-live
Engagement doesn’t end at launch. Innovise stays accountable through production and is available for ongoing technical support and leadership.
We help clients build independence
Innovise is willing to help clients build their own internal engineering teams when that’s the right move — including hiring guidance, mentorship, and a structured transition plan. The business model is not built on creating dependency.
Direct access, always
No account managers, no project coordinators between the client and the engineer. The person on the first call is the person doing the work.

Services and engagement models
What we build and do
–	Full-stack software development
–	Fractional technical leadership and CTO advisory
–	System integrations
–	Systems design and architecture
–	DevOps and cloud infrastructure
–	UX and interface design
–	Custom website builds (focused on performance, conversion, and long-term maintainability)
How we engage
Embedded development team
Short or long-term engagements where Innovise functions as the client’s full engineering department. Can scale up or down depending on the initiative.
Technical retainer
A senior engineer monitoring systems and available for strategic questions on an ongoing basis. Designed for businesses that need steady technical oversight without a full engagement.
Technology and security audit
A structured, one-time entry point for companies not yet ready for a full engagement. Produces a clear-eyed assessment of existing systems, risks, and opportunities.

Voice and tone guidelines
All Innovise content should reflect the following principles:
Directness
Lead with outcomes and concrete specifics. Avoid hedging, filler, and corporate warmth.
Specificity over adjectives
Describe quality through specifics (senior engineers, direct access, no handoffs) rather than through adjectives (boutique, world-class, best-in-class).
No jargon
Avoid: “end-to-end solutions,” “best-in-class,” “leverage,” “synergy,” “modern methodologies,” “industry best practices.”
Earned trust
Innovise earns trust through honesty about how it works, not through claims about being the best.
Formatting
Sentence case for all headings. No unnecessary capitalization.

